---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="DEVS — Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for DEVS (begindevs.com). How we collect, use, and protect your data.">
  <main id="main" class="px-6 py-32 md:py-40">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-legal">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <p>
        DEVS ("we," "us," or "our") operates the website
        <a href="https://begindevs.com">begindevs.com</a> (the "Service"). This
        Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and
        your rights regarding that information.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Information you provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email address</strong> — collected when you join our early access list.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        As DEVS grows, we may collect additional information such as account
        details, usage data, and payment information. This policy will be updated
        before any new data collection begins.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To send DEVS product updates and launch announcements (you can unsubscribe at any time)</li>
        <li>To improve the Service</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will never sell your personal data to third parties.</p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We currently use the following third-party services that may process your data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Brevo</strong> — email delivery for updates and announcements</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting and content delivery</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        As the platform launches, additional services (such as payment
        processing and authentication providers) will be added. This policy will
        be updated accordingly before those services are introduced.
      </p>
      <p>Each service operates under its own privacy policy. We only share the minimum data required for each service to function.</p>

      <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your data for as long as your account is active or as needed to
        provide the Service. If you delete your account, we will delete your
        personal data within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and associated data</li>
        <li><strong>Export</strong> your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Unsubscribe</strong> from marketing emails at any time</li>
        <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing of your data (EU/EEA residents under GDPR)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To unsubscribe, use the link in any email we send. Additional data rights requests will be supported when the full platform launches.</p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use essential cookies required for authentication and session
        management. Analytics tools may set additional cookies. You can control
        cookie behavior through your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        DEVS is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal data from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected
        data from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you
        of significant changes by email or by posting a notice on the Service.
        Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the
        updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        To unsubscribe from emails, use the unsubscribe link included in every
        email we send. A dedicated contact email will be provided when the full
        platform launches.
      </p>

      <div class="back-link">
        <nav class="legal-links" aria-label="Legal page links">
          <a href="/">&larr; Back to DEVS</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/privacy" aria-current="page">Privacy Policy</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose-legal {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .prose-legal h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal .meta {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-legal h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-soft);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .prose-legal ul {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .prose-legal a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .prose-legal a:hover {
    color: white;
  }
  .back-link {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }
  .back-link a {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .back-link a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .legal-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .legal-links span {
    opacity: 0.45;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
</style>
